r 2022 (1.39%).  “This means that in the month of December 2022, the general price level was 0.32% higher relative to November 2022.  “The percentage change in the average CPI for the twelve months ending December 2022 over the average of the CPI for the previous twelve months period was 18.85%, showing 1.89% increase compared to the 16.95% recorded in December 2021.”  The National Bureau of Statistics (NBS) says inflation rate, measured by the Consumer Price Index (CPI), has further dropped to 15.37  per cent in December 2017 from 15.90 per cent recorded in November of the same year. In "News" By ELIZABETH AMIHOR The National Bureau of Statistics, NBS, said inflation rate rose to 15.6 percent in December last year, after recording eight months consecutive decline  in 2021. This represents 0.2 percent point rise when compared with 15.4 percent recorded in November 2021. The Bureau disclosed this today in its… In "News" Inflation rate hit 17yrs high, rises to 21.47% in November In "News"